Re: Jokes about learning Japanese
by furrykef » Fri 08.21.2009 2:31 am To me, "nai" sounds like "no hay" (pronounced like "no I" in English), which is Spanish for "there aren't any" -- which is of course one of the meanings of "nai".No hay libros = 本は無い = There aren't any books.
