Re: Jokes about learning Japanese
by furrykef » Fri 08.21.2009 7:51 pm They aren't pronounced identically, but the only difference between them is that "no hay" has an "o" in it. You'd probably still be understood if you said "Nai nada aquí", although it'd sound sloppy and possibly foreign.Also, since I'm a foreign speaker, they probably sound much more alike to me than they do to native speakers, since they have a much more refined sense of the distinction between vowels in their language. I'm lucky if I can properly transcribe something spoken in Spanish, let alone actually understand it. - Kef
Founder of Learning Languages Through Video Games.Also see my lang-8 journal, where you can help me practice Japanese (and Spanish, and Italian!)
